# Maison Parfum Component Patterns

Reusable patterns for building consistent, maintainable UI. Prefer composition over duplication. Never recreate layout primitives that already exist.

## Project Structure

```
components/
  ui/          → primitives (Button, cards, SectionTitle)
  layout/      → Navbar, Footer, Container
  sections/    → homepage and marketing sections
  product/     → product detail components
  cart/        → cart page components
  wishlist/    → wishlist page components
  checkout/    → checkout page components
```

## Section Pattern

Every marketing or catalog section must use:

- `Container` for horizontal padding and max width
- `SectionTitle` when the section has a heading (subtitle + title)

Standard structure:

```tsx
<section className="py-20">
  <Container>
    <SectionTitle subtitle="..." title="..." />
    {/* section content */}
  </Container>
</section>
```

Guidelines:

- Page-level headers may use inline eyebrow + `h1` where `SectionTitle` (`h2`) is not appropriate
- Alternate section backgrounds with `bg-[var(--muted)]` sparingly
- Use consistent vertical padding within page types
- Do not wrap sections in extra divs that duplicate `Container` behavior

## Card Pattern

All cards must follow the shared visual pattern:

- `rounded-3xl`
- `border border-[var(--border)]`
- `bg-white`
- Consistent inner padding (`p-5` or `p-6`)
- No decorative shadows

Existing card components to reuse:

- `ProductCard`
- `CollectionCard`
- `TestimonialCard`

Guidelines:

- Use consistent spacing between card elements (`mt-1`, `mt-2`, `mt-4`)
- Fixed image heights only when needed for grid alignment
- Hover: subtle image scale or opacity — never aggressive transforms
- Link cards by wrapping with `Link`, not duplicating card markup
- Extract a shared card shell only when a third variant is needed

## Layout Primitives

Never duplicate these — always import and compose:

| Primitive | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Container` | Page width, horizontal padding |
| `SectionTitle` | Section headings |
| `Button` | All CTAs and form submits |
| `Navbar` | Site header |
| `Footer` | Site footer |

Do not create alternate wrappers for max-width, padding, or section headings.

## Composition Over Duplication

Before creating a new component:

1. Check `components/ui/` for an existing primitive
2. Check `components/sections/` for a similar section pattern
3. Extend via props or children rather than copying markup
4. Extract shared patterns only after the second real duplication

Prefer:

- Composing `Container` + `SectionTitle` + domain component
- Passing data as props with strict TypeScript interfaces
- Small, focused components with single responsibility

Avoid:

- Copy-pasting grid layouts across sections
- Inline card markup when `ProductCard` or siblings apply
- Local layout helpers that mirror `Container`

## Styling Rules

- Tailwind CSS only
- No inline styles
- Use design tokens from `globals.css`:
  - `--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, `--secondary`, `--muted`, `--border`
  - `--font-heading`, `--font-body`, `--radius`
- Use `font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)]` for serif headings
- Prefer token-based colors over hardcoded grays

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first: base styles for small screens, scale up with `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`
- Grids: `grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3` for card collections
- Stack forms and sidebars vertically on mobile
- Test navigation, grids, and checkout flows at narrow widths

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML (`main`, `section`, `nav`, `article`, `button`)
- Label icon-only buttons with `aria-label`
- Associate form inputs with `<label>` or `sr-only` labels
- Provide visible or `focus-visible` focus states
- Use `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls`, and `aria-pressed` where state matters
- Guard persisted client state with `useHydrated()` to prevent hydration mismatches

## TypeScript

- Strict typing on all props via interfaces
- No `any`
- Colocate prop types with components
- Import domain types from `types/` (e.g. `Product`, `Collection`)

## Client vs Server

- Default to Server Components
- Add `"use client"` only when hooks, events, or browser APIs are required
- Keep data fetching in `lib/api/` — never in UI components
- Zustand stores are client-only; read with hydration guards when rendering persisted state

## Checklist for New Components

- [ ] Uses `Container` if it is a section
- [ ] Uses `SectionTitle` if it has a section heading
- [ ] Follows shared card pattern if displaying a card
- [ ] Uses design tokens, not ad-hoc colors
- [ ] Mobile-first responsive
- [ ] Accessible labels and focus states
- [ ] Typed props interface
- [ ] No duplicated layout primitives
